          <idx><h>HOMEWORK: Terrance Tao and the Fields Medal</h></idx>
      There is no Nobel Prize in mathematics unfortunately.
      However, there is the much more prestigious Fields Medal given to outstanding mathematicians no older than 40 once every four years,
      awarded by the International Mathematics Union (IMU) \cite{IMU},
    </p>
